                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-355-off1995 t18260914-355-crimeloc1998"></join>. The prisoner came to the shop and looked at this calico, among several other articles - he wanted three yards of calico for a shilling - I refused; he was there a quarter of an hour, and went out; we then missed the calico, and went after him; it was found in his basket - he said it must have fallen into his basket.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. PHILLIPS. Q. He came back quietly; A. Yes - a great many pieces of calico were on the counter, and several persons had passed; the prisoner said where he lived, and how he got his living, which we found correct; my mistress was called down, and said it might be an accident.</p>
